      • valueOf

        public static SpatialRepresentationType valueOf​(String code)
        Returns the spatial representation type that matches the given string, or returns a new one if none match it. More specifically, this methods returns the first instance for which name().equals(code) returns true. If no existing instance is found, then a new one is created for the given name.
        Parameters:
        code - the name of the code to fetch or to create.
        Returns:
        a code matching the given name.
